<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget.Delete" Title="Delete method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget">ILogTarget</PageRef> ->
    Delete
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>Delete</TypeRef> method destroys the log target object.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        Targets are normally owned by <TypeRef>ILogTarget::unique_ptr</TypeRef> and transferred to <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.AddLogTarget">LogManager.AddLogTarget</PageRef>. In that case, the custom deleter calls this method automatically.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[virtual void Delete() = 0;]]></Code>
  </Section>
